questiontext.text:
A graphical representation of the Fourier transform of the signal s(t) below will exhibit two peaks. Estimate the positions of these peaks on the frequency axis.



Give your answer to 2 d.p.
Higher Frequency: {1:NUMERICAL:=5.00:0.01#Good job!!~*#Incorrect}
Lower Frequency: {1:NUMERICAL:=0.08:0.01#Good job!!~*#Incorrect}

generalfeedback.text:
The signal consists of the sum of two sine waves, with periods of 0.2 second and 12 seconds. Frequency and Period are related by the equation:

$$ \small f = \frac{1}{T} $$

Thus the peaks will be observed at frequencies of 1/2 Hz and 1/12 Hz (=0.08 Hz).
